WEBVTT

00:06.590 --> 00:08.801
<i>John Gotti, life in prison...</i>

00:09.218 --> 00:11.220
<i>...no chance of parole.</i>

00:11.721 --> 00:16.726
<i>We've seen prosecutions in Florida
and elsewhere of top Mob figures.</i>

00:18.019 --> 00:20.187
What are you doing?
Put that back.

00:22.857 --> 00:27.361
<i>What's the situation on the ground
today, right now, in the Mob?</i>

00:27.528 --> 00:28.529
<i>Confusion...</i>

00:29.447 --> 00:30.614
<i>...instability...</i>

00:31.490 --> 00:33.534
<i>- ...vacuum at the top.
- What caused it?</i>

00:33.784 --> 00:35.619
Your sister's ass.

00:36.120 --> 00:38.164
<i>Policy over two decades...</i>

00:38.414 --> 00:40.082
<i>...to behead the crime families.</i>

00:40.332 --> 00:42.752
<i>But wasn't it, at least in part...</i>

00:43.210 --> 00:45.963
<i>...a disregard
within the Mob itself...</i>

00:46.839 --> 00:50.051
<i>...of the rules that served
the old dons so well?</i>

00:50.301 --> 00:52.344
- If the shoe fits.
<i>- No doubt.</i>

00:52.595 --> 00:55.222
Sil. Cheer me up, babe.

00:56.223 --> 01:00.686
Just when I thought I was out,
they pull me back in.

01:02.104 --> 01:04.732
Is that Pacino or is that Pacino?
Spitting image.

01:04.982 --> 01:06.901
<i>- Vincent Rizzo.
- Yes.</i>

01:07.151 --> 01:09.862
<i>Former soldier in the Genovese family.</i>

01:10.112 --> 01:12.990
<i>Government witness
turned best-selling author.</i>

01:13.199 --> 01:15.451
<i>Do you agree with U.S. Attorney Braun?</i>

01:15.659 --> 01:16.911
<i>The party's over.</i>

01:17.453 --> 01:20.706
<i>- He is a wiseguy. Elaborate.
- It's not like it was.</i>

01:20.956 --> 01:23.375
- Cloning.
- Mexicans are huge in that.

01:23.626 --> 01:26.587
- Fascinating.
- Because they work as parking valets.

01:27.505 --> 01:29.632
<i>Do I mean that organized crime...</i>

01:31.967 --> 01:34.011
<i>...will go the way of the dodo bird?</i>

01:35.930 --> 01:38.849
- What the fuck are you talking about?
- Mexicans.

01:39.100 --> 01:40.935
- What about them?
- Cell phones.

01:41.185 --> 01:43.938
I'm not talking
about cloning cell phones.

01:44.188 --> 01:46.732
I'm talking about fucking sheep!
Science.

01:46.941 --> 01:49.360
I tell my kids,
"Only God can make a life."

01:49.610 --> 01:53.405
A guy here asks, "What if they had
cloned Princess Di?"

01:53.697 --> 01:57.368
<i>But you know, the heydey?
You know, the Golden Age...</i>

01:57.576 --> 01:59.078
<i>...or whatever, of the Mob?</i>

01:59.537 --> 02:00.704
<i>That's gone.</i>

02:01.205 --> 02:03.124
<i>And that's never coming back.</i>

02:03.707 --> 02:06.836
<i>They have only themselves to blame.</i>

02:07.086 --> 02:09.463
They pay this <i>chiacchierone</i>
by the word?

02:09.713 --> 02:11.048
<i>Drug trafficking.</i>

02:11.257 --> 02:13.843
- Oh!
<i>- I think it ruined everything.</i>

02:14.135 --> 02:17.388
<i>You're looking at a mandatory
35 to life in prison.</i>

02:17.638 --> 02:20.808
<i>Guys started to rat
so they could avoid prosecution.</i>

02:21.016 --> 02:23.435
What's going on
with that Princess Di?

02:24.353 --> 02:27.189
Do you think the royal family
had her whacked?

02:27.982 --> 02:30.109
Last time I take a limo in Paris.

02:30.359 --> 02:31.986
Like you were ever in Paris.

02:32.486 --> 02:33.737
I went for a blowjob.

02:34.321 --> 02:38.117
Your mother was working the bonbon
concession at the Eiffel Tower.

02:38.409 --> 02:41.620
You hear what I told him?
"I went over for a blowjob.

02:41.871 --> 02:44.957
Your mother was working
at the Eiffel Tower."

02:45.207 --> 02:47.626
I got a list of people
I wouldn't want cloned.

02:47.877 --> 02:51.463
The mayor of New York, that's
the guy least likely to get cloned.

02:51.714 --> 02:56.427
<i>So the code of silence, the</i> omertà,
<i>or whatever, just went by the boards.</i>

02:56.677 --> 03:00.764
<i>You're always gonna have
organized crime. Always.</i>

03:00.973 --> 03:04.351
<i>As long as the human being
has certain appetites...</i>

03:04.602 --> 03:07.229
<i>...for gambling, pornography
or whatever.</i>

03:07.479 --> 03:11.192
<i>Someone's always gonna surface
to serve these needs. Always.</i>

03:11.442 --> 03:15.863
Just when I thought I was out,
they pull me back in.

05:09.059 --> 05:10.936
- You got DVD players?
- Don't hurt me.

05:11.186 --> 05:13.856
Only people who get hurt
are the jerk-offs.

05:14.106 --> 05:16.150
Now step down, nice and easy.

05:17.318 --> 05:19.236
He's got the DVD players.

05:19.445 --> 05:21.530
Quick and painless.
Not to hurt you.

05:21.780 --> 05:23.198
You gotta tie me up.

05:23.407 --> 05:26.243
- You gonna be a jerk-off?
- My boss'll think I'm in on it.

05:26.535 --> 05:29.705
We look like we want a merit badge?
We travel with rope?

05:29.955 --> 05:33.000
I've got some in the cab.
Please, I need this job.

05:33.250 --> 05:34.460
Okay, get the rope.

05:34.710 --> 05:39.048
I don't know who gave the route,
but there's no way I'd go unscathed...

05:39.256 --> 05:41.342
- ...without being fired.
- You want to be scathed?

05:41.550 --> 05:44.470
So it looks like I didn't
give up without a struggle.

05:49.391 --> 05:51.393
- Oh!
- That's cool. Thank you.

05:52.853 --> 05:53.896
That's enough.

05:54.688 --> 05:55.856
No, wait.

05:56.815 --> 05:57.941
Oh!

05:58.942 --> 06:00.944
Ow! That's good!

06:01.195 --> 06:02.196
- Scathed?
- Scathed.

06:02.404 --> 06:03.697
He's scathed.

06:08.827 --> 06:11.580
Mr. Miller, my science teacher,
he got his car stolen.

06:11.955 --> 06:14.166
You're kidding.
From where? His house?

06:14.375 --> 06:17.002
Mm-mm. His parking spot at school.

06:17.461 --> 06:19.546
A Saturn. He only had it a year.

06:19.797 --> 06:21.715
The security people are a joke.

06:21.965 --> 06:26.053
Did you hear what A.J. just said?
Mr. Miller's car got stolen.

06:26.553 --> 06:28.472
Refresh my memory. Who is he?

06:28.722 --> 06:31.392
He's your son's science teacher.

06:34.478 --> 06:35.646
You're up early.

06:35.938 --> 06:38.065
He just bought that car a year ago.

06:38.273 --> 06:39.733
So? Insurance will pay.

06:39.942 --> 06:41.693
They don't give full value.

06:41.944 --> 06:44.321
These poor teachers,
they don't make a lot.

06:44.571 --> 06:47.032
So he can work his summer vacation.

06:48.158 --> 06:49.535
You could help find it.

06:49.785 --> 06:53.455
I thought I told you I changed my name
from LoJack to Soprano.

06:53.789 --> 06:55.457
Laugh. I'd pee in my pants.

06:55.958 --> 06:58.544
Pussy's got the body shop.
He couldn't ask?

06:58.794 --> 06:59.962
I'm late.

07:01.004 --> 07:03.841
- What are you getting in science?
- D-plus.

07:05.342 --> 07:08.220
- See what I can do.
- That's not what I meant.

07:08.512 --> 07:10.681
He's gotta work for his grades.

07:21.442 --> 07:23.026
I'm going back to bed.

07:23.360 --> 07:25.028
- Bye, Dad.
- See you later.

07:27.698 --> 07:28.949
Here, eat this.

07:37.708 --> 07:39.626
Technology comes to the Bing!

07:39.877 --> 07:41.920
Hey, where you been?

07:42.171 --> 07:45.132
- Come on.
- Let's go.

07:45.424 --> 07:47.301
- Hey, is the load here?
- Yeah.

07:50.512 --> 07:52.514
If Serge calls, I'll be back.

07:52.723 --> 07:56.602
These new phones, hold, conference,
sometimes I get confused.

07:57.352 --> 07:58.770
How complicated is it?

07:59.021 --> 08:00.439
Answer the phone, take the message.

08:00.689 --> 08:03.275
Voice mail only comes on
if you let it ring.

08:03.525 --> 08:05.068
Jesus Christ, Georgie.

08:14.495 --> 08:16.622
I hear there's not as many titles
as on laser.

08:16.872 --> 08:17.915
There's more coming.

08:18.165 --> 08:21.084
My internist said the picture's
not that different.

08:21.335 --> 08:23.504
But the sound...
Way improved.

08:24.004 --> 08:28.634
Good. Nothing beats popping up some
corn and listening to <i>Men in Black.</i>

08:28.884 --> 08:31.553
- Fuck it!
- It's the damn wires, that's all!

08:31.803 --> 08:34.348
I'll hook it up.
I used to be an installer.

08:39.478 --> 08:41.772
Why can't you be nice to Brendan?

08:42.022 --> 08:43.649
We discussed that.

08:47.236 --> 08:49.696
I was gonna come looking.
It's the guy.

08:49.947 --> 08:51.156
It's Serge?

08:51.406 --> 08:52.991
I'll take it over there.

08:59.331 --> 09:00.707
Serge?

09:04.336 --> 09:06.421
Press "hold" when you transfer a call.

09:06.672 --> 09:08.006
I'm sorry, Tony.

09:12.469 --> 09:14.096
Now he's not gonna call back.

09:14.346 --> 09:17.933
Brendan's a good earner, T.
This jack was his plan.

09:18.183 --> 09:20.352
He's a good kid,
but I don't like meth.

09:24.273 --> 09:26.191
Fuck, I gotta call my mother.

09:32.906 --> 09:35.117
- Hello?
<i>- Hello, Ma?</i>

09:35.367 --> 09:38.579
Oh, look who calls.

09:38.829 --> 09:41.748
<i>- How you doing?</i>
- I was wondering when you'd call.

09:42.249 --> 09:45.544
You can stop wondering now.
This is it, I'm calling you.

09:46.503 --> 09:49.256
I called yesterday.
You were supposed to call me back.

09:49.506 --> 09:52.134
I phoned your house.

09:52.384 --> 09:56.096
Some operator answered. I couldn't
understand a word she was saying.

09:56.346 --> 09:59.600
That's not an operator,
that's an answering machine.

09:59.850 --> 10:02.853
Oh, fancy, fancy.

10:03.061 --> 10:06.398
Here, let me turn the heat off
under these mushrooms.

10:12.029 --> 10:13.905
You and Mom are like peas in a pod.

10:14.114 --> 10:17.743
She can't master the phone,
but she's 70. What's your excuse?

10:25.667 --> 10:27.419
What is she doing now?

10:35.052 --> 10:36.845
Oh, my God.

10:38.055 --> 10:40.474
<i>- Oh, my God.</i>
- Ma!

10:42.351 --> 10:43.727
<i>Ma!</i>

10:47.022 --> 10:48.523
<i>Hey, Ma!</i>

10:51.526 --> 10:54.446
- Oh, my God!
<i>- Ma!</i>

10:54.780 --> 10:55.781
Where is she?

10:56.740 --> 10:58.784
- Who is this?
<i>- It's Anthony!</i>

10:59.034 --> 11:01.203
The mushrooms, they're on fire!

11:01.453 --> 11:04.081
Get the fire extinguisher
under the sink!

11:04.331 --> 11:07.459
Oh, my God!
The wall's getting all black!

11:07.709 --> 11:09.586
Ma, hang up and call 911.

11:10.212 --> 11:11.672
The guy's on the second line.

11:11.880 --> 11:14.966
<i>- Aren't you coming over?</i>
- You press "hold," goddamn it.

11:15.509 --> 11:17.511
I can't, I'm 40 minutes away.

11:17.719 --> 11:20.597
You hang up and you call 911.
Leave the house.

11:20.847 --> 11:23.433
Look at how I live!

11:23.684 --> 11:25.435
Ma, hang up and call 911.

11:33.944 --> 11:36.238
My mother's got a fire in the kitchen.

11:36.488 --> 11:39.449
- Oh, my God.
<i>- She's calling 911. Go there.</i>

11:39.700 --> 11:42.953
- I'm on my way.
- Thank you, baby. I know you're busy.

11:43.870 --> 11:46.081
Serge, Serge.

11:46.331 --> 11:47.416
I can't talk now.

11:48.208 --> 11:50.544
I gotta go to an outside line.

11:52.629 --> 11:54.756
All right. I'll call you back.

11:55.006 --> 11:56.508
Is your mom okay?

11:56.717 --> 11:58.385
Shit cannot go on like this.

11:59.928 --> 12:02.347
Hey, T. Hey, T.

12:02.931 --> 12:06.101
This teacher, his car,
you got a plate number?

12:07.394 --> 12:08.812
Call my wife.

12:14.401 --> 12:15.819
- Have a nice day.
- Thanks.

12:16.069 --> 12:17.362
No problem.

12:24.953 --> 12:26.121
Ma.

12:27.622 --> 12:30.542
I wish you'd let me
get somebody to help you.

12:30.792 --> 12:34.045
- You shouldn't be alone.
- Help me what?

12:35.380 --> 12:38.341
- With the housework.
- I have my ways.

12:39.342 --> 12:42.512
A stranger could care less
about doing it right.

12:43.680 --> 12:47.184
Can I tell you something though, Ma?
You need company.

12:47.851 --> 12:50.771
Don't start with that nursing-home
business again.

12:51.021 --> 12:54.649
This is not a nursing home.
It is a retirement community.

13:01.656 --> 13:05.327
You want me to make you <i>pastina?</i>
Something in your stomach?

13:09.790 --> 13:12.334
Ma, now, I've told Tony...

13:12.584 --> 13:16.171
...and I've told you many times.

13:17.005 --> 13:18.507
You can come live with us.

13:19.382 --> 13:21.593
I know when I'm not wanted!

13:23.887 --> 13:28.016
I invited you to share my home.
If you want me to beg, that's different.

13:29.893 --> 13:34.731
Leave this place
that my husband and I shared?

13:35.982 --> 13:38.109
Well, change can be a positive.

13:39.152 --> 13:41.196
He was a saint.

13:44.950 --> 13:49.329
That son of mine, is he
still having those fits?

13:50.622 --> 13:54.751
They're not fits, Ma.
They're anxiety attacks.

13:55.043 --> 13:56.878
You know, he's on medication.

14:03.343 --> 14:06.471
What BMW's charging us for paint?
<i>O trippa di zia.</i>

14:07.681 --> 14:11.226
- It's been that way for six months.
- When was I last here?

14:13.144 --> 14:14.354
Hey.

14:16.314 --> 14:17.941
We maybe caught a break.

14:18.191 --> 14:22.863
Watchung Avenue said some guys brought
a Saturn trying to load it for parts.

14:23.113 --> 14:26.741
Are you saying this car's for Tony
and leave it all in one piece?

14:26.992 --> 14:29.786
Yeah, sure.
It's for the kid's teacher.

14:30.704 --> 14:35.542
My guy said one of those goofballs
had a uniform on from Buttfucks.

14:36.710 --> 14:39.504
Whatever, the coffee shop.
I guess the guy works there.

14:39.754 --> 14:41.006
Watchung and what?

14:44.843 --> 14:46.553
I'm fucking Rockford here.

14:50.849 --> 14:54.936
Decaf cappuccino Primo, non-fat
Magnifico, double espresso regulare.

14:55.186 --> 14:56.271
I'll take you here.

14:58.356 --> 15:02.944
I think I'll have an espresso.
Paul, you want anything?

15:03.194 --> 15:04.696
They got any just coffee?

15:04.946 --> 15:07.365
Our café du jour
is New Zealand Peaberry.

15:08.366 --> 15:10.368
<i>Madonna</i>. Whatever.

15:10.619 --> 15:12.329
That's $4.20. Pick up there.

15:12.579 --> 15:15.248
One medium du jour,
one single espresso.

15:15.457 --> 15:16.708
Here, keep it.

15:18.418 --> 15:19.836
Honey, let me ask you.

15:20.045 --> 15:23.715
My wife was in the body shop around
the corner the other day.

15:24.507 --> 15:28.386
The guy in front of her leaves
and she sees he dropped...

15:28.595 --> 15:30.096
...his money clip.

15:30.347 --> 15:33.558
But he was already gone.
We'd like to give it back.

15:33.808 --> 15:37.437
She said he was wearing
a uniform like that there.

15:37.729 --> 15:40.482
Real black hair.
Tall? Little earring.

15:40.732 --> 15:42.567
These stores are everywhere.

15:43.234 --> 15:44.861
Yeah, tell me about it.

15:49.908 --> 15:52.994
Fucking Italian people.
How'd we miss out on this?

15:53.244 --> 15:56.581
- What?
- Fucking espresso, cappuccino.

15:56.831 --> 16:00.126
We invent it and these
cocksuckers are getting rich.

16:00.377 --> 16:01.670
Isn't it amazing?

16:01.920 --> 16:04.172
It's not just money.
It's a pride thing.

16:04.422 --> 16:08.593
All our food, pizza,
calzone, buffalo mozzarella...

16:08.802 --> 16:09.803
...olive oil.

16:10.053 --> 16:11.763
These fucks had nothing.

16:11.972 --> 16:14.891
They ate <i>puzzi</i> before
we gave them our cuisine.

16:15.100 --> 16:18.979
But this, this is the worst.
This espresso shit.

16:19.187 --> 16:20.188
Take it easy.

16:22.440 --> 16:25.527
She finally agreed
to have somebody come in days.

16:25.777 --> 16:30.907
Carmela called an agency, and they
sent over this Trinidadian woman.

16:32.075 --> 16:35.620
But no matter what I do,
I feel guilty.

16:35.870 --> 16:36.913
Why?

16:40.583 --> 16:43.503
The real reason is,
I can't let her live with us.

16:43.962 --> 16:47.132
That doesn't seem practical,
given her personality.

16:48.967 --> 16:51.845
Well, it's my wife.
She won't allow it.

16:52.262 --> 16:54.180
Where are your sisters in this?

16:54.806 --> 16:58.685
They cut it off with her long ago.
No way she's bunking with them.

16:58.977 --> 17:03.314
So you're carrying all this guilt
when your mother is clearly someone...

17:03.565 --> 17:06.901
...who has difficulty maintaining
any relationship.

17:09.404 --> 17:11.197
But she's my mother.

17:11.489 --> 17:15.493
You're supposed to take care of your
mother. She's a little old lady.

17:15.869 --> 17:17.287
Not to you.

17:17.537 --> 17:19.080
She's very powerful.

17:19.497 --> 17:20.582
Bullshit.

17:20.832 --> 17:23.293
You accord this "little old lady"...

17:23.501 --> 17:26.546
...an almost mystical ability
to wreak havoc.

17:26.796 --> 17:30.383
Let me tell you. You definitely
don't want to get her started.

17:31.301 --> 17:35.513
There are some people who are not
ideal candidates for parenthood.

17:36.264 --> 17:38.933
Come on. She's an old sweetie-pie.

17:39.517 --> 17:43.730
What were some of the good
experiences you remember as a child?

17:43.938 --> 17:45.690
The loving warm ones?

17:57.160 --> 18:00.413
One time we were down at the shore.

18:00.622 --> 18:03.875
About '68, '69, the whole family.

18:04.876 --> 18:09.172
My father, he tripped and fell down
the stairs, and we were all laughing.

18:09.464 --> 18:13.093
The whole family was laughing.
My mother was laughing.

18:15.095 --> 18:17.263
Any other loving experiences?

18:17.889 --> 18:19.724
Hey, she's a good woman.

18:20.266 --> 18:22.560
She put food on the table every night.

18:23.853 --> 18:27.315
I'm the ungrateful fuck.
I come here, complain about her...

18:27.524 --> 18:30.860
...and I let my wife exclude her
from my home.

18:45.041 --> 18:46.501
Hey, Ma!

18:50.547 --> 18:52.048
- You Perrilyn?
- Yes.

18:52.215 --> 18:53.216
Tony Soprano.

18:53.383 --> 18:54.634
Ah.

18:56.094 --> 18:57.595
- How you doing?
- I'm fine.

19:00.056 --> 19:04.477
Oh, Livia, your son is here!
And isn't he a handsome thing.

19:05.353 --> 19:07.564
And look what he brought.

19:10.775 --> 19:13.444
All right, listen.
Let's get one thing straight.

19:13.695 --> 19:18.616
In the hours you're here taking care
of my mother, no ganja. Okay?

19:18.867 --> 19:22.162
Hey, Ma, <i>fiori.</i>

19:23.371 --> 19:27.375
I'm not dead, unfortunately for some.

19:28.001 --> 19:30.086
The tall ones are delphiniums.

19:30.378 --> 19:33.047
You know, Frankie Valli
when he visits Jersey?

19:33.715 --> 19:35.425
This is the florist he uses.

19:35.675 --> 19:37.510
Aren't they beautiful?

19:37.760 --> 19:39.929
Want me to put them on the table?

19:40.180 --> 19:43.850
You make sure the bottom
of the vase isn't wet.

19:44.100 --> 19:46.978
Mr. Tony, would you like
some tea or something?

19:47.187 --> 19:49.480
Coke, thanks.

19:55.361 --> 19:57.197
So how's it going today?

19:59.073 --> 20:00.366
She's stealing.

20:01.326 --> 20:02.368
Who?

20:02.785 --> 20:04.704
That <i>ditsoon,</i> who.

20:05.830 --> 20:10.126
That beautiful plate Aunt Settimia
took from that restaurant in Rome.

20:10.293 --> 20:11.294
It's gone.

20:12.921 --> 20:15.423
I don't know.
She seems like a nice person.

20:15.673 --> 20:18.176
She doesn't fool me for a second.

20:24.224 --> 20:25.266
You sure she stole it?

20:26.726 --> 20:29.312
You didn't give it
to one of the relatives?

20:30.146 --> 20:33.900
You keep forcing your possessions
on people, thinking you're gonna die.

20:34.484 --> 20:36.110
I wish it was tomorrow.

20:38.738 --> 20:42.033
And she's so forward too.
Who does she think she is?

20:42.867 --> 20:45.495
She's happy, Ma. She's singing.

20:45.745 --> 20:48.164
Anthony, I don't want her around here.

20:48.915 --> 20:50.583
I can manage somehow.

20:50.792 --> 20:53.211
No, I'm not giving in
to you this time.

20:53.586 --> 20:55.380
She stays.

21:02.512 --> 21:04.597
Your uncle called here
looking for you.

21:05.139 --> 21:06.182
Uncle Jun?

21:06.849 --> 21:08.393
He sounded agitated.

21:11.854 --> 21:14.941
Jackie, tell them to leave
Comley trucking alone.

21:15.608 --> 21:17.902
Didn't know it was a Comley truck.

21:18.111 --> 21:22.699
For 21 fucking years, Comley's put
food on my table, protection money.

21:23.283 --> 21:25.868
- Chris didn't know going in.
- Bullshit.

21:26.286 --> 21:28.913
Want my DVD?
You can watch <i>Grumpy Old Men.</i>

21:29.163 --> 21:31.499
- You gonna be a fucking funny boy now?
- Hey!

21:32.250 --> 21:33.751
You Sopranos.

21:33.960 --> 21:38.840
You hope you and your uncle can settle,
not be invited to a fucking sit-down.

21:39.090 --> 21:41.467
You got a crew of cowards
you don't control.

21:41.676 --> 21:43.177
Here we go.
Here we go.

21:43.469 --> 21:44.637
You got a ruling?

21:49.809 --> 21:52.437
The kids make restitution to Junior.

21:52.687 --> 21:54.022
Done. It's done.

21:59.068 --> 22:01.321
Christopher Moltisanti's
a fucking loose...

22:01.571 --> 22:03.197
You get him out of a sick bed?

22:03.448 --> 22:04.699
Hey, fuck that shit.

22:08.953 --> 22:11.914
Giacomino, how you feeling?

22:12.290 --> 22:16.336
I may be acting boss while your old
man's a guest of the government...

22:16.586 --> 22:19.839
