my bowels. They don't obey.

22:21.466 --> 22:23.384
Ah, the fucking chemo.

22:25.762 --> 22:28.181
Maybe I should name a successor.

22:28.389 --> 22:31.017
This day and age?
Who wants the fucking job?

22:33.644 --> 22:36.522
Your mom tells me you got
a girl coming in to help.

22:37.774 --> 22:38.816
That's good.

22:40.526 --> 22:43.196
All right, I gotta go.

22:44.113 --> 22:46.115
I'll see you soon.

22:49.327 --> 22:50.703
We okay?

22:50.912 --> 22:52.163
All right.

22:55.875 --> 22:58.419
The smoke he hires for his own mother.

23:02.673 --> 23:04.258
Hey, Mikey, how's the boy?

23:04.467 --> 23:06.344
- What boy?
- The one you sleep with.

23:06.844 --> 23:08.221
Oh.

23:08.596 --> 23:09.597
I'm just kidding.

23:09.847 --> 23:11.182
How's Jun treating you?

23:11.432 --> 23:15.728
We're covering our nut. Your nephew
retarded? Likes to play with trucks?

23:15.978 --> 23:18.648
What if Jerry Lewis heard
you talking like that?

23:18.898 --> 23:21.567
No, that's muscular dystrophy, Tony.

23:21.943 --> 23:26.155
Too bad they don't have a telethon
for fuckface-itis. They find a cure?

23:27.073 --> 23:28.282
I'm just kidding you.

23:28.533 --> 23:31.160
Come on, you're a good sport.
You all right?

23:31.411 --> 23:33.079
- Yeah.
- You all right?

23:33.287 --> 23:35.331
- Yeah.
- I'll see you later.

23:39.001 --> 23:42.255
- Double cappuccino suprema.
- Double cappuccino suprema.

23:43.840 --> 23:46.384
Thanks. Excuse me.

23:47.885 --> 23:50.972
A guy fitting the description
does work in this branch.

23:51.180 --> 23:54.851
His name is Edguardo Arnaz.
Him and his gay lover both work here.

23:55.101 --> 23:56.811
And I got the address.

23:58.855 --> 24:01.399
- Paulie, are you listening to me?
- Yeah.

24:02.275 --> 24:04.110
Again with the rape of the culture.

24:04.318 --> 24:07.697
Can we go find these Spice Girls
and get this over with?

24:10.700 --> 24:12.660
Two small café du jours.

24:25.047 --> 24:26.674
That's it!

24:26.924 --> 24:28.468
What happened?

24:29.427 --> 24:31.053
Beats me.

24:31.304 --> 24:33.097
Did you say something to her?

24:33.306 --> 24:36.142
I know how to talk to people.

24:36.726 --> 24:38.269
These blacks.

24:38.603 --> 24:41.230
Who knows what they'll
take the wrong way.

24:41.439 --> 24:42.857
So she's gone!

24:46.402 --> 24:48.821
<i>Traffic and weather
on this Tuesday morning.</i>

24:51.282 --> 24:55.536
<i>There's a delay as you
get out of the Lincoln Tunnel.</i>

24:55.786 --> 24:59.373
<i>About a 25-minute delay if you're
approaching near Deer Route 3.</i>

24:59.582 --> 25:02.793
<i>The queue beginning just before
the Bergen Viaduct.</i>

25:03.753 --> 25:06.797
You had orders. Why didn't you
pay his restitution?

25:07.048 --> 25:11.093
Restitution, okay. But you
know how much your uncle wants? $15.

25:11.344 --> 25:14.388
You got the wrong truck,
that's what happened.

25:18.434 --> 25:21.938
I didn't notice you rushing
to give back your fucking DVD player.

25:22.188 --> 25:23.940
I'm enjoying it very much.

25:24.148 --> 25:27.818
I screened <i>The Bank Dick</i> last night.
"Did you warble, my little wren?"

25:28.444 --> 25:29.529
I'm not gonna pay it.

25:30.530 --> 25:32.323
- Oh, yeah?
- I'm serious.

25:32.532 --> 25:35.159
Serious is what happens
if you don't pay, by me.

25:35.952 --> 25:40.039
In my thoughts, I use the technique
of positive visualization.

25:40.289 --> 25:42.375
How come I always feel undermined?

25:42.625 --> 25:47.755
By what I did on the Triborough Towers
alone, I should've been made. Boom!

25:48.464 --> 25:49.465
Hmm.

25:49.674 --> 25:51.467
I'm fucking serious, Tony.

25:51.759 --> 25:53.010
The books are closed.

25:53.386 --> 25:55.263
Did you talk to Jackie about me?

25:56.264 --> 25:59.100
They're not accepting
any new members, okay?

26:00.518 --> 26:04.230
You know, you got a reputation
for immaturity...

26:04.480 --> 26:08.276
...and it's not helping, not paying
the tributes the acting boss demands.

26:08.526 --> 26:10.278
Acting boss, my ass.

26:10.486 --> 26:14.865
Everybody knows you really run things
since Jackie became the "chemo-sabi."

26:16.826 --> 26:19.870
Open the fucking door.
Open the fucking door!

26:23.624 --> 26:26.210
Ow. Oh.

26:29.422 --> 26:30.715
All right.

26:30.965 --> 26:32.717
All right. Fuck it.

26:32.967 --> 26:34.468
But 15 grand is too much!

26:34.719 --> 26:36.137
I'll tell you what.

26:37.263 --> 26:40.558
You give me the 15 K,
I'll talk to Uncle Junior...

26:40.808 --> 26:43.227
...and maybe I can get it
to around 10.

26:51.861 --> 26:53.237
One more thing.

26:53.654 --> 26:57.617
You leave Comley Trucking and every
other item that belongs to Jun...

26:57.825 --> 27:01.787
...including his hemorrhoid doughnut,
the fuck alone. Got it?

27:02.913 --> 27:04.081
Yeah.

27:14.300 --> 27:16.761
"Did you warble, my little wren?"

27:17.011 --> 27:19.096
What will his commission will be?

27:19.347 --> 27:21.599
Two, three grand. Ten to Junior.

27:21.807 --> 27:24.935
We're lucky we net 500 bucks
from the whole thing.

27:26.228 --> 27:27.229
Ah!

27:37.239 --> 27:38.282
Who is it?

27:40.284 --> 27:41.285
What?

27:50.252 --> 27:52.046
Mr. Arnaz?

27:52.296 --> 27:53.631
What do you want?

27:53.881 --> 27:56.842
You seen a schoolteacher's
Saturn around here?

28:00.471 --> 28:01.639
Come here!

28:03.140 --> 28:05.101
Anybody else here, Desi?

28:05.351 --> 28:07.895
- Eddie, I'm ready.
- Yep.

28:08.229 --> 28:09.230
Here comes Lucy.

28:09.480 --> 28:12.233
Those people at the airport
shuttle are always late.

28:13.109 --> 28:14.193
- Uh!
- Eddie!

28:14.443 --> 28:16.821
You boys drove off in the wrong car.

28:17.071 --> 28:19.990
We ain't saying shit
until there's an attorney.

28:20.241 --> 28:22.743
Well, go ahead. Make a statement.

28:22.993 --> 28:25.037
I got fucking Johnny Cochran here!

28:37.550 --> 28:39.635
You boys put a crimp in my week.

28:40.177 --> 28:42.722
- Ah, <i>mannaggia!</i>
- Get over there.

28:44.056 --> 28:46.892
Hey, Puss, here's the fucking set.

28:48.352 --> 28:49.353
Look.

28:50.312 --> 28:52.440
Fucking car's been chopped. Useless.

28:52.690 --> 28:53.733
That's not it.

28:53.983 --> 28:57.236
Then why is that car inside there?
That Dodge?

28:57.486 --> 29:01.782
Why is that motherfucker wearing the
fucking plate number I had all week?

29:02.032 --> 29:04.577
- I don't know.
- Here's what's gonna happen.

29:05.119 --> 29:08.706
The two of youse are climbing over that
fence and shagging those plates.

29:08.956 --> 29:10.499
But the razor wire.

29:10.750 --> 29:15.880
Then one of you stays with us while
the other goes and gets another Saturn.

29:24.472 --> 29:27.808
- On the lookout for ducks?
- Know the old man pretty good.

29:28.058 --> 29:31.937
Don't look so sad. Remember how
pissed you were about the pool filter?

29:33.689 --> 29:37.151
They were special, them coming here,
huh? Don't you think?

29:37.401 --> 29:38.652
I wasn't into it.

29:42.865 --> 29:44.909
What time's Grandma getting here?

29:45.159 --> 29:47.411
She had to drive
Fanny to the doctor's.

29:47.661 --> 29:50.998
Then she is picking up my parents
and they're coming here.

29:51.916 --> 29:54.251
They're each bringing
some <i>antipasto.</i>

29:55.586 --> 29:59.298
I complain about my mother,
about how she just sits at home...

29:59.548 --> 30:00.966
...and feels sorry for herself.

30:01.217 --> 30:06.013
But she's always ready to drive those
friends of hers that can't drive.

30:07.389 --> 30:10.434
I'm proud of her. It gives me hope.

30:31.372 --> 30:33.624
It's getting chilly out here.

30:33.874 --> 30:37.545
Make plenty of noise
before you open the front door.

30:38.170 --> 30:39.922
You never know who's in there.

30:40.422 --> 30:43.926
There's my <i>Star-Ledger</i>. Thanks.

30:44.176 --> 30:48.931
Oh, this street,
another pain in the ass.

30:53.394 --> 30:56.230
She broke her wrist
on the steering column.

30:56.522 --> 30:58.065
A minor concussion.

30:59.066 --> 31:00.651
What about the other woman?

31:02.862 --> 31:03.863
Hip.

31:08.158 --> 31:10.619
We were at the hospital till 2 a.m...

31:10.870 --> 31:16.000
...talking to her doctor
and the staff gerontoligist.

31:16.417 --> 31:18.752
They say she shouldn't
live alone anymore.

31:21.755 --> 31:24.174
She can't manage the telephone.

31:26.635 --> 31:28.846
Yet you say she's healthy and alert.

31:29.555 --> 31:31.265
Like a bull.

31:32.474 --> 31:33.767
Why?

31:34.268 --> 31:36.270
I'm just thinking.

31:36.478 --> 31:41.400
I know there are other doctors there,
but you know from your own life...

31:41.650 --> 31:46.113
...that depression can cause
accidents, poor performance or worse.

31:46.363 --> 31:48.157
So, what are you saying?

31:48.365 --> 31:50.659
Unconsciously she tried
to whack her friend?

31:51.118 --> 31:55.247
It's interesting that you would even
take that from what I said.

31:57.124 --> 32:01.170
Either way, she could need a change
in her living situation...

32:01.378 --> 32:02.713
...be around more people.

32:03.422 --> 32:05.299
We were looking at Green Grove.

32:05.549 --> 32:06.967
It's a beautiful facility.

32:07.509 --> 32:12.056
It's more like a hotel
at Cap d'Antibes.

32:13.891 --> 32:15.267
Yeah.

32:16.936 --> 32:21.148
- But to her it's a nursing home.
- She needs to see the distinction.

32:21.398 --> 32:25.486
That, in fact, she's embarking
on a rewarding chapter.

32:26.153 --> 32:30.574
I know seniors who are inspired
and inspiring.

32:36.288 --> 32:38.415
You're not forgetting us, buddy?

32:40.793 --> 32:42.169
Ladies.

32:48.175 --> 32:50.761
Hey, Kenny Portugal said
to say hello.

32:51.011 --> 32:52.596
Oh, yeah. Kenny.

32:57.351 --> 32:59.269
The fuck is with this cocksucker?

32:59.812 --> 33:02.606
Back up! Mr. Scorsese, good evening.

33:02.856 --> 33:05.484
Whoa! Wow!

33:05.985 --> 33:07.403
Marty!

33:07.778 --> 33:09.530
<i>Kundun!</i> I liked it.

33:19.456 --> 33:21.792
So my boy at Comley...

33:22.334 --> 33:24.712
...said there's a load
of Italian suits.

33:24.920 --> 33:28.674
Those unload fast.
Mario'll take the whole load.

33:29.299 --> 33:32.219
He says shipment moves
Thursday at 6 a.m.

33:35.305 --> 33:38.684
Give me one good reason
I should not jack this truck.

33:39.101 --> 33:43.647
It's Junior's own fault. He gives us
no choice except to do it again.

33:43.897 --> 33:45.691
Taking that outrageous tribute.

33:45.941 --> 33:50.195
He shits on our heads, we're
supposed to say thanks for the hat.

33:50.863 --> 33:54.491
I'm getting nowhere playing
by the rules. Fuck Tony.

33:54.742 --> 33:56.869
"The books are closed." Blow me.

33:57.077 --> 33:58.328
That's some true shit.

33:58.579 --> 34:01.623
They're not confirming any
new made guys. How come?

34:01.832 --> 34:05.544
Fucking chaos. Nobody knows
who's running things anymore.

34:05.794 --> 34:10.382
Guys don't know who to make payments
up the ladder to in some cases.

34:10.966 --> 34:14.011
I'm talking about the year 2000.
The millennium.

34:14.762 --> 34:16.638
Where do we go from here?

34:25.939 --> 34:26.940
Oh.

34:27.649 --> 34:29.902
Ma, this Virginia ham...

34:30.486 --> 34:32.488
Go on, get yourself some more.

34:32.696 --> 34:34.490
No, I'm full.

34:34.740 --> 34:36.241
It's good, though.

34:37.034 --> 34:39.078
You never let me feed you.

34:41.955 --> 34:45.042
So getting back
to what we were talking about.

34:45.292 --> 34:47.086
- You want that lamp?
- Lie down.

34:47.294 --> 34:52.091
That lamp, that's real ormolu. You
know what that's worth when it's new?

34:52.341 --> 34:54.593
We're fixed good lamp-wise, thank you.

34:54.802 --> 34:56.970
Take it and take the Barcalounger.

34:58.180 --> 35:01.892
Somebody's gotta take
this stuff before I die.

35:02.684 --> 35:05.604
Otherwise there's gonna be
a lot of stuff here...

35:05.813 --> 35:08.899
...that the junkman's gonna
have to cart off to the dump.

35:09.149 --> 35:14.154
Mom, you're not gonna die. Your
stuff won't be hauled off to the dump.

35:14.446 --> 35:18.784
Plan for the future. The most rewarding
chapter of your life's coming up.

35:19.701 --> 35:23.163
- You know my good jewelry?
- The stuff Dad gave you.

35:23.664 --> 35:26.917
Some of those pieces came right
out of Cartier's window.

35:27.835 --> 35:29.837
Listen, Carm doesn't want it.

35:30.129 --> 35:31.630
Not now.

35:31.880 --> 35:36.969
We want you to live long and wear your
sparklers to grandkids' graduations.

35:37.219 --> 35:39.930
I gave it all
to your cousin Josephine.

35:41.181 --> 35:42.850
The fuck?
The good jewelry?

35:43.100 --> 35:45.060
She always admired it.

35:45.644 --> 35:46.979
They don't have much.

35:47.229 --> 35:51.150
You gave her Cartier rings,
and you give me a vibrating chair?

35:51.400 --> 35:55.112
Your wife never showed
any interest in my jewels.

35:55.362 --> 35:58.866
She never complimented me
on any of it, as I remember.

35:59.116 --> 36:04.246
Before you do more damage to yourself
or your grandchildrens' inheritance...

36:04.454 --> 36:06.206
