personal effects.

40:02.442 --> 40:04.903
All right, Ma, sign right here.

40:15.705 --> 40:16.998
Yes?

40:17.624 --> 40:20.210
Mr. Soprano, do you have
an Uncle Junior?

40:20.585 --> 40:22.003
He tracked me down here?

40:22.712 --> 40:24.840
Line two? Here you go.

40:25.132 --> 40:26.633
I'll call him back.

40:26.883 --> 40:29.719
He'll return the call. He did?

40:30.387 --> 40:35.142
It's urgent. She said he sounded
upset. He'll call back.

40:38.353 --> 40:43.108
Livia, did you ever hear the old
Italian saying? My aunt used to go:

40:43.358 --> 40:46.319
<i>"Col tempo la foglia
di gelso diventa seta."</i>

40:52.117 --> 40:53.577
What's that mean, Bonnie?

40:53.785 --> 40:57.747
Time and patience change
the mulberry leaf to silk.

41:12.345 --> 41:13.763
You gonna be all right?

41:14.681 --> 41:16.141
Yeah, sure.

41:16.725 --> 41:18.435
Thanks for all your help.

41:20.812 --> 41:22.314
I'll make us a nice lunch.

41:22.522 --> 41:25.317
I've got some fantastic
prosciutto in there.

41:28.445 --> 41:29.696
Hello?

41:29.905 --> 41:32.115
Yeah. It's Christopher.

41:33.533 --> 41:34.534
Yeah.

41:34.743 --> 41:37.496
I've been calling for hours.
Call me on an outside line.

41:52.469 --> 41:55.096
T, don't get mad.
There's been a little shit.

41:55.305 --> 41:57.516
<i>- I had nothing to do with it...</i>
- Spit it out!

41:58.558 --> 42:00.101
Brendan hit Comley again.

42:00.644 --> 42:02.062
He what?

42:04.147 --> 42:07.817
- And the driver, you know...
- No, I don't know.

42:08.527 --> 42:12.405
He caught some friendly fire
or something and he's gone.

42:13.782 --> 42:15.033
Oh, fuck!

42:15.242 --> 42:17.452
What do we do, T?
Brendan didn't fence the load.

42:17.661 --> 42:21.039
He's thinking it was Mario
who dimed us to Junior last time.

42:21.289 --> 42:22.624
Fuck!

42:41.017 --> 42:42.477
Hey, Ton.

42:42.686 --> 42:45.605
Sorry you have to wreck
your Saturday like this.

42:47.941 --> 42:51.444
You boys. You boys, I'll tell you.

42:54.864 --> 42:56.783
It's beautiful stuff, though.

42:57.033 --> 42:58.868
- Ton, I'm so sorry.
- Shut up.

42:59.119 --> 43:01.871
Just so you realize I had
nothing to do with this.

43:02.080 --> 43:04.624
- Ton, that's true. He stood home.
- Shut up.

43:05.500 --> 43:06.876
Stood home?

43:08.670 --> 43:12.924
Did you do anything to stop it?
Did you offer any guidance?

43:13.758 --> 43:16.595
What do we mean when we say
leadership, hm?

43:17.053 --> 43:20.890
Part of it's the crank. But I'm
going into detox, swear on my mother.

43:21.141 --> 43:24.811
Brendan, shut the fuck up.
You want to get me clipped?

43:27.856 --> 43:29.107
What are we gonna do?

43:29.441 --> 43:34.446
You're gonna put these suits back
in the truck and give them back.

43:34.654 --> 43:35.905
Fuck!

43:36.114 --> 43:38.408
Then call my uncle
and tell him it's done.

43:40.160 --> 43:41.494
What about the dead guy?

43:41.745 --> 43:45.081
Prod him with a stick.
Light a candle to St. Anthony.

43:45.332 --> 43:46.958
But I think you're fucked.

43:50.045 --> 43:51.296
Ton...

43:52.130 --> 43:55.592
...what if this didn't go back?
Would it be a problem?

43:59.929 --> 44:02.349
I don't see you assholes putting
that rack, and that rack...

44:02.557 --> 44:04.851
...and this rack here
back in the truck.

44:13.652 --> 44:17.739
Just when I thought I was out,
they pull me back in.

44:17.906 --> 44:19.032
Hmm!

44:20.950 --> 44:23.119
Hey, Mr. Miller, your car is back.

44:23.370 --> 44:27.165
My wife dropped me off
and there it was, in my parking spot.

44:27.374 --> 44:29.501
My Uncle Pussy
helped my dad locate it.

44:29.709 --> 44:31.127
Uncle Pussy?

44:31.378 --> 44:33.838
He's in the car business.

44:34.422 --> 44:38.009
I don't know what to say to your
dad, I mean, thanks of course.

44:38.218 --> 44:40.095
It's nice and clean too.

44:40.512 --> 44:42.389
Whoa, different keys!

44:42.597 --> 44:47.602
It's probably too much to hope my
papers are still inside the trunk.

44:47.977 --> 44:49.896
It's a different color.

44:50.105 --> 44:52.399
Whoa. Ooh.

44:54.567 --> 44:56.569
My dad's a hero.

45:56.880 --> 46:00.383
<i>Did you actually lose
consciousness like with the ducks?</i>

46:00.759 --> 46:02.010
No.

46:03.136 --> 46:08.266
Just a shortness of breath and
the white spots in my field of vision.

46:08.975 --> 46:10.226
Improvement.

46:10.769 --> 46:12.687
Because I'm sad to put my mother away?

46:13.188 --> 46:15.940
Sad is good. Unconscious isn't.

46:17.692 --> 46:21.446
She'll be in very good hands.
You've done the best for her.

46:23.406 --> 46:25.283
She won't speak to me.

46:26.659 --> 46:30.079
That is sad.
But whose choice is that?

46:30.330 --> 46:32.540
Somehow that doesn't make it
any better.

46:33.750 --> 46:37.295
Can you admit to yourself that yes,
you're sad...

46:38.213 --> 46:40.423
...but you're angry and full of rage?

46:40.673 --> 46:41.925
I'm sad.

46:42.133 --> 46:44.385
It's hard to admit that...

46:44.886 --> 46:48.348
...you may have feelings of hatred
towards your mother, isn't it?

46:48.598 --> 46:50.433
You're out of your tree.

46:52.268 --> 46:54.687
Listen carefully.
Of course you love her.

46:55.730 --> 47:00.443
What I'm trying to say is, own
the anger instead of displacing it.

47:00.693 --> 47:04.864
Otherwise it defines your life.
It needs to be acknowledged.

47:05.114 --> 47:08.660
It's a good thing time is up.
I don't want to talk to you anymore.

47:08.910 --> 47:10.161
"Hate your mother."

47:40.275 --> 47:41.734
Shit.

47:43.236 --> 47:45.280
A what do you call it? A menu.

47:46.614 --> 47:49.868
Press two if you know
your party's extension.

47:50.076 --> 47:52.996
Is that an operator
or an answering machine?

47:53.580 --> 47:55.874
Let's see. Hello? Hello?

47:56.624 --> 47:57.876
Hello?

47:58.543 --> 47:59.878
Hello?

48:01.296 --> 48:03.298
Press zero. Hello?

48:04.132 --> 48:06.593
Hello? Hello?

48:10.179 --> 48:11.347
Ooh.
